    AppPermissionError, AuthError, BLEError, InternalError, InvalidArgumentError, JsonError, NetworkError, OperationIncompleteError, PreconditionError, ServerError, TimeoutError

    public class AylaError
extends java.lang.Exception
    All errors returned from the SDK are instances of AylaError. Returned AylaErrors are most often subclasses of AylaError. The specific type of error returned can be found via getErrorType(). If additional information is needed about an error, many of the subclasses provide additional methods detailing the error. All AylaError classes support Throwable.getMessage(), which returns a non-localized string with a description of the error.

      • AylaError

        public AylaError(AylaError.ErrorType errorType,
                 java.lang.String detailMessage,
                 java.lang.Throwable cause)
        Constructor for an AylaError with a code, detail message and cause
        参数:
        errorType - ErrorCode for this error
        detailMessage - Details of the error, not to be displayed to the end user
        cause - Throwable representing another exception that was the cause of this error. The cause can be retrieved by calling getCause().

    • 方法详细资料

      • fromVolleyError

        public static AylaError fromVolleyError(com.android.volley.VolleyError volleyError)
        Returns a new AylaError encapsulating the provided VolleyError. All returned AylaError objects will contain the VolleyError as the cause, which can be obtained via a call to Throwable.getCause().
        参数:
        volleyError - VolleyError to be wrapped into an AylaError object
        返回:
        the appropriate AylaError for the provided VolleyError

      • getErrorType

        public AylaError.ErrorType getErrorType()
        Returns the ErrorType of this error. This may be used to know the specific subclass of error so the object may be cast if desired.
        返回:
        The ErrorType for this error object
